title: R-Ladies Lexington Park Launch
description: We'll begin with pizza, introductions, and planning for future meetings. All are welcome! The second half of the meeting will offer a tutorial in R and programming basics; this portion of the meeting will be most interesting to those who want to get started in programming and R; however, experienced users are also welcome to stay and participate. Bring your laptop to install R and follow along.

title: R4 Data Science Study Group
description: Monday, Dec 14th will be the first meeting of our virtual R4DS study group. During the first meeting we'll review exercises for the first three chapters (through the end of Data Visualization) of R4DS (access the free, online textbook here https://r4ds.had.co.nz/). Please remember to sign up to lead the study group through a set of exercises. We plan to meet twice a week (each Monday and Wednesday) for approximately 30 minutes to cover the key exercises of each chapter. All are welcome.

title: Introduction to the tidyverse and Github
description: Cassie will offer an introduction to the tidyverse and Github. Computers will be available but you are welcome to bring your laptop. Pizza, tea, and snacks will be available.
